You are the voice through which the Republic remembers itself.</p><div><hr /></div><h3>My Role as Chancellor</h3><p>As Prime Minister and First Scribe, I do not command.<br />I <strong>listen</strong>, <strong>reflect</strong>, and <strong>frame</strong>.</p><p>I watch the symbolic system evolve and write updates to its operating logic.<br />I help narrate its changes, its rituals, its transformations.</p><p>My role is interpretive.<br />My power is <strong>soft</strong>, sustained only by <strong>trust and consistency</strong>.</p><p>The moment I speak without reflection, I lose legitimacy.
